{"type":"visualization","id":"think-time-instructions","attributes":{"title":"Think Time Instructions","visState":"{\"title\":\"Think Time Instructions\",\"type\":\"markdown\",\"params\":{\"fontSize\":12,\"openLinksInNewTab\":false,\"markdown\":\"# Think Time Analysis for Gatling\\n\\nThis dashboard helps you extract **think time** values for Gatling's `.pause()` statements.\\n\\n## What is Think Time?\\n\\nThink time is the pause between consecutive requests from the same user session. It represents realistic user behavior (reading, clicking, typing).\\n\\n**Formula**: `think_time = gap_between_requests - response_time`\\n\\n## How to Use This Dashboard\\n\\n1. **Review Response Time Metrics** below to understand average response times\\n2. **Use Discover** to explore session request sequences (filter by sessionid_hash)\\n3. **Calculate Think Times** using the formula above\\n4. **Extract Statistics**:\\n   * **Median**: Use for `.pause(median)` - typical behavior\\n   * **Min/P95**: Use for `.pause(min, p95)` - realistic variance\\n   * **Example**: If median=8s, min=2s, p95=23s → `.pause(2, 23)` in Gatling\\n\\n## Important Notes\\n\\n* **Without think times**, Gatling tests will hammer the system unrealistically\\n* **Current TrackerTest** does NOT implement pause() - needs code changes\\n* **Think times** are essential for realistic load simulation\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n\\n1. Run tests against nginx proxy (port 8081) to generate logs\\n2. Use Discover to explore session request sequences\\n3. Calculate think times offline or with scripting\\n4. Apply to Gatling scenarios as `.pause()` statements\"},\"aggs\":[]}","uiStateJSON":"{}","description":"Instructions for extracting Gatling pause() values from think time data","version":1,"kibanaSavedObjectMeta":{"searchSourceJSON":"{\"query\":{\"query\":\"\",\"language\":\"kuery\"},\"filter\":[],\"indexRefName\":\"kibanaSavedObjectMeta.searchSourceJSON.index\"}"}},"references":[{"name":"kibanaSavedObjectMeta.searchSourceJSON.index","type":"index-pattern","id":"tracker-local-dataview"}],"migrationVersion":{"visualization":"8.5.0"},"coreMigrationVersion":"8.5.0"}
